			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>So I debated sharing this for awhile since this is a mostly anonymous forum.  -Though I, like many here have been a member of the community since the early 2000's.<br />
<br />
But the pics I just got from my cardiologist are just too cool not to share, heh.  I find them pretty amazing at least.<br />
<br />
So, yeah, I had a heart attack February 25th.  Heart disease is rampant on my father's side of the family, and because of this our family doctor was constantly checking for indicators and warning signs with me, and none ever presented themselves.  :(<br />
<br />
My blood pressure has always been perfect, my cholesterol levels have always been normal, I'm in good health otherwise, lift weights 3 times per week.  So it came as a complete shock.  I was in complete denial.  In the E.R. I was telling them they need to double check because I've struggled with acid reflux most of my life and I was certain it was a symptom of that, not a heart attack.  But it was, almost a complete blockage of my left circumflex artery.<br />
<br />
They shot me up with some kind of dye to visually inspect the blockage, and then installed a catheter in my right wrist and reached the blockage that way and placed a stent.  I was up and walking later that afternoon.  They placed me on a bunch of meds to lower blood pressure, thin the blood, and help with cholesterol.  They've reduced some of them today on my follow up appointment, where I also got these cool pics lol.  Before the placement of the stent:<br />
